From: edevkit
Subject: [PATCH 3/3] subsys/dap: make dap_process_vendor_cmd weakly overridable

Applications that need to expose custom CMSIS-DAP vendor commands
(0x80..0x9F) currently have no path: dap_process_vendor_cmd() is a
static function inside cmsis_dap.c that returns ID_DAP_INVALID for
every vendor command. There's no Kconfig hook or callback registry
either.

Make it weakly defined so applications can provide a strong override
in their own .c files. The default behavior (return INVALID) is
unchanged — apps that don't override see exactly today's surface.

The change is two lines: drop `static` (widen linkage from internal
to external) and add `__weak` so the default is overridable. The
function signature stays the same; the call site in dap_process_cmd
is unchanged.

Use case: edevkit's nRF5340 recover/erase/write/read ops are exposed
as vendor commands 0x84..0x8B. With this patch, the app file
firmware/projects/edev_dapv2_zephyr/src/nrf53/nrf53_vendor.c can
provide its own dap_process_vendor_cmd that dispatches to those
handlers. No upstream commits depend on the function being static.

diff --git a/subsys/dap/cmsis_dap.c b/subsys/dap/cmsis_dap.c
index ce26e8a30f3..9c221553c50 100644
--- a/subsys/dap/cmsis_dap.c
+++ b/subsys/dap/cmsis_dap.c
@@ -819,8 +819,9 @@ static uint16_t dap_writeabort(struct dap_link_context *const ctx,
 	return retval;
 }
 
-/* Process DAP Vendor command request */
-static uint16_t dap_process_vendor_cmd(struct dap_link_context *const ctx,
+/* Process DAP Vendor command request — weakly defined so applications
+ * can override it with their own vendor command set (0x80..0x9F). */
+__weak uint16_t dap_process_vendor_cmd(struct dap_link_context *const ctx,
 				       const uint8_t *const request,
 				       uint8_t *const response)
 {
